=Description=

Paul D. Fernhout:

"In some of Sturgeon's other writings he also addresses networking issues and
social change, but not so simply as the Xanadu short story. For example, in
the novel "To Marry Medusa",
 http://www.amazon.com/Marry-Medusa-Theodore-Sturgeon/dp/0375703721

he puts into conflict a p2p consciousness made of individual people vs. an
single amazing unity of most of the rest of the galaxy's organisms."


